141	// stops the growth tasks (and repo-tidy) from self-triggering on the fleet's own
142	// maintenance commits — the feedback loop where last night's baselining commit fires
143	// tonight's growth-extract/dedup/tidy on a repo that has no new lesson or landed work.
144	// The baselining worker writes a subject-initial `Baseline:` / `Baselining:` (mount +
145	// wiring refresh), `Claudinite baseline…`, or a `seed default-on` commit — match them
146	// all, subject-anchored so a real "baseline benchmark" feature commit still counts.
147	const HOUSEKEEPING_MESSAGE = /\[skip ci\]|(^|\n)\s*baselin(e|ing)\b|claudinite baselin|seed default-on/i;
